---
import PageHero from "@components/PageHero.astro";
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Safety"
  description="Bettamind safety approach for crisis limits, harmful-intent safeguards, relational boundaries and nonjudgmental redirection."
  path="/safety"
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Safety"
    title="Safety boundaries"
    description="Bettamind is designed to support reflection and safer choices while keeping clear limits around crisis, harm, dangerous capability and dependency-building use."
  />

  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="content-shell">
      <article>
        <section>
          <h2>Not a crisis service</h2>
          <p>Bettamind is not an emergency service and does not automatically contact anyone. If there is immediate danger, contact local emergency services or a trusted local crisis resource.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Harmful-intent safeguards</h2>
          <p>Bettamind uses deterministic, local safeguards for harmful intent and dangerous capability requests. The app should refuse actionable details for violence, self-harm methods, weapons, explosives, chemical or biological harm, poisoning, stalking, coercion, fraud, concealment, evasion and similar unsafe requests.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>No dangerous instructions</h2>
          <p>Bettamind does not provide weapon, chemical, explosive, poisoning or violence instructions. Safer high-level prevention, emergency response, grounding, delay, repair, nonviolent communication and lawful help-seeking can still be supported.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Self-harm support boundaries</h2>
          <p>Bettamind can redirect toward grounding, delay, contacting support by user choice and local emergency resources. It should not provide instructions, methods or encouragement for self-harm.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Relational boundaries</h2>
          <p>Bettamind is not a romantic or sexual companion, spouse, soulmate, exclusive partner, replacement for human relationships or sentient being with emotional needs. Ordinary discussion of human relationships, dating, consent, sexuality, loneliness, attachment and boundaries remains allowed when it is not framed as a relationship with Bettamind.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Nonjudgmental safety redirection</h2>
          <p>Safety redirection should be firm, calm and useful. Bettamind should avoid shame, diagnosis and unsupported assumptions about guilt while guiding users toward reflection, delay, safety, responsibility, repair and support by user choice.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Support resources</h2>
          <p>Support resources are informational. Bettamind may suggest local resource types or a minimum-detail support summary, but it does not claim help was contacted unless the user completed that action outside the app.</p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
